    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Regarding this email:
<a href="http://www.nabble.com/Help-with-Zend_Xmlrpc_Value-tf3776546s16154.html#a10678821">http://nabble.com/Help-with-Zend_Xmlrpc_Value-tf37â€¦</a></p>

<p>The current date format used inside your class files is:
{{2007-05-18T22:31:31+02:00}}</p>

<p>However, the XML-RPC implementation of the ISO8601 requires this:
{{20070518T22:31:31}}</p>

<p>Omitt all dashes and TZ. I know this is misleading, since PHP's {{date('c', $foo)}} prints "another" ISO8601 date.</p>

<p>But if you look at the <a href="">www.xmlrpc.com/spec</a>" rel="nofollow"&gt;spec, you see the above examples - let alone all implementations of XML-RPC (in PHP, Python, Java, etc.) which I have checked over the last two days all format the date according to the spec and not as returned by {{date('c', $foo)}}.</p>

